            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">10. A 54-year-old known hypertensive male presented with a 3-day history of shortness of breath. The patient reported feeling unwell with a sharp pain in the left side of the chest and loss of appetite. His clinical findings included a heart rate of 117 bpm, blood pressure of 97/85 mmHg, temperature 37.2°C and a respiratory rate of 22 bpm.Respiratory examination showed reduced air entry and hyper-resonance on percussion. The most likely diagnosis is:</p>"
