            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">19. Haemoptysis<br />\nA 44-year-old woman is brought to accident and emergency after becoming ill at<br />\nthe airport after a flight from Australia. She presents with mild pain that causes her<br />\nto catch her breath and has been coughing blood-stained sputum. On examination,<br />\nher respiratory rate is 25, heart rate 100 bpm and blood pressure is 130/85 mmHg.<br />\nThe most appropriate management is:</p>"
