            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">21. A 35-year-old man complains of a three-month history of intermittent excruciating headaches. They are very variable and occur from once a month to three times a week. The headaches are associated with extreme anxiety and sweating. On examination, the patient’s blood pressure is 152/95 mmHg and during palpation of the abdomen the patient’s skin flushes red. The most likely diagnosis is:</p>"
